CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 1, 1960, pg. 21, reads: "Everybody's Happy - There wasn't a sad face in all of Pittsburgh Sunday night as the Pittsburgh Pirates, new National League champions, took part in a gigantic victory celebration, following the team's arrival from Milwaukee. Enjoying the festivities from convertibles are, left photo: Gene Baker and his lovely wife Ella... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball player Gene Walker, and his wife Ella Walker, riding in back of car in parade for celebration of 1960 National League Championship, Downtown
